<% layout('layouts/boilerplate') %>
<main class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="my-3" style="font-size: 7vh;">FAQ</h1>
    <div class="accordion" id="accordionFAQ">
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingQ1">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#q1"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="q1">
                    What is the purpose of this website?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="q1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingQ1" data-bs-parent="#accordionFAQ">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    It's pretty simple: This website is my playground for practicing web development. Besides that, I
                    will develop productivity tools that might help people in their job, studies or wherever they need
                    to be productive.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingQ2">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#q2"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="q2">
                    Why do I need to sign up?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="q2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingQ2" data-bs-parent="#accordionFAQ">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    You don't need to :) Most of the tools will be available for users with or without an account. If
                    you use apex9.io on a regular basis, I highly recommend signing up as you will be able to connect
                    things (e.g. your shortlinks) with your account.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingQ3">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#q3"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="q3">
                    Are the tools free to use?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="q3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingQ3" data-bs-parent="#accordionFAQ">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    Of course :) I'm not planning on making money with this website in the foreseeable future.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingQ4">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#q4"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="q4">
                    Is the code of the tools open source?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="q4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingQ4" data-bs-parent="#accordionFAQ">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    Generally speaking, the code is not open source. But if you really really want the code of a tool,
                    let me know and we'll find a
                    solution :)
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingQ5">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#q5"
                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="q5">
                    I found a bug, what should I do?
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="q5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingQ5" data-bs-parent="#accordionFAQ">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    Ooopsie... Well, as I am still practicing web development, bugs will occur. If you find one,
                    please contact me and tell me what you found. (Future Tool Spoiler Alert: As a little "thank
                    you gesture", you will get 49 pixel credits to draw whatever you want on the <a
                        href="../whiteboard">community whiteboard</a>.)
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</main>